Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveAs The Kardashians return in a newly-packaged reality TV show, billionaire Kim Kardashian has revealed that her ex-husband, Kanye West, told her that her “career was over”.
This was revealed in the first official trailer of the show, which is scheduled to debut in April.
In the trailer, Kim is seen telling her sisters that her ex-husband, Kanye West, had told her that her “career was over.” The circumstances in which he said it has however not been revealed.
ALSO READ: Kim Kardashian divorce from Kanye West finalised
Also, in the trailer, Kim expressed how hard it is to deal with Kanye, saying, “It is really hard with Kanye.”
Kanye and Kim have been involved in public squabbles recently over the parenting of their four children; North, Saint, Chicago and Psalm.
Kim’s romantic relationship with Saturday Night Live star, Pete Davidson, is also a source of grief for the rapper, who steadily kept bashing Davidson on social media and threatening bodily harm.
